videos.description: UCF's Richie Grant picks off South Florida QB Chris Oladokun, but Nick Roberts answers for USF with an interception of McKenzie Milton.
videos.headline: South Florida, UCF trade INTs in 1st quarter

videos.description: South Florida's defense goes offside and UCF's McKenzie Milton takes advantage with a 14-yard touchdown strike to Gabriel Davis in the 1st quarter.
videos.headline: Milton gives UCF lead with 14-yard TD pass

videos.description: Greg McCrae finds a hole in the South Florida defense and runs 40 yards up the middle to extend UCF's lead in the 2nd quarter.
videos.headline: UCF's McCrae goes untouched for 40-yard TD

videos.description: McKenzie Milton points to the crowd after UCF, South Florida players and fans show concern for his serious leg injury.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Milton points to crowd during emotional scene after injury) 2018/11/23 ESHEET

videos.headline: Milton points to crowd during emotional scene after injury

videos.description: South Florida's Chris Oladokun finds Johnny Ford over the middle for a 34-yard touchdown to cut into UCF's lead in the 3rd quarter.
videos.headline: USF narrows deficit with 34-yard TD pass

videos.description: Greg McCrae bounces to the outside and sprints up the sideline for a 39-yard touchdown, his 2nd score vs. South Florida.
videos.headline: UCF's McCrae scores 2nd TD

videos.description: UCF's Greg McCrae breaks through the South Florida defense and scores from 31 yards out for his third rushing touchdown of the game in the 4th quarter.
videos.headline: McCrae runs free to complete hat trick

videos.description: UCF head coach Josh Heupel does not have an update on QB McKenzie Milton's injury, but is proud of the team's performance vs. South Florida.
videos.headline: Heupel: Milton injury 'breaks your heart'
